Operatives of the Ogun State Police Command have arrested a 38-year-old man, Daniel Udoh for allegedly stabbing his lover’s husband to death.
 
The suspect, according to the police, was arrested on Saturday, January 7 in the Ota area of the state.  “The remains of the victim were subsequently deposited at Ifo general hospital mortuary for post mortem examination,” Oyeyemi said.
 
The PPRO said the commissioner of police, Lanre Bankole has directed that the suspect be transferred to the homicide section of the state criminal investigation and intelligence department, for further investigation, with the view to charging him to court as soon as the investigation is concluded. 